Here are the MSTest patterns for each scenario:

## 1. Windows-only (platform condition)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("Windows")]
public void Registry_ReadsExpectedValue()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Test requires Windows.");
        return;
    }

    // ... registry access code
}
```

Or filter at run time: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=Windows"` on non-Windows CI.

## 2. Skip in CI (no GPU available)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void Render_ProducesExpectedFrame()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
        return;
    }

    // ... GPU test
}
```

In CI, exclude with: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"`

## 3. Flaky external API (retry with `[Retry]` — MSTest v3+)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public async Task WeatherApi_ReturnsForecast()
{
    var result = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync("Seattle");
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
    Assert.IsTrue(result.Days.Count > 0);
}
```

> `[Retry(maxCount)]` was introduced in **MSTest v3.6+**. For older versions, wrap in a manual retry loop or mark flaky tests with `[TestCategory("Flaky")]` and handle in CI policy.

## 4. Cleanup even on failure (`[TestCleanup]`)

```csharp
private string? _tempFile;

[TestMethod]
public void Export_WritesToTempFile()
{
    _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");

    var result = MyExporter.Process(_tempFile);
    Assert.AreEqual("OK", result.Status);
}

[TestCleanup]
public void Cleanup()
{
    if (_tempFile != null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
    {
        File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```

`[TestCleanup]` runs after **every** test method in the class, regardless of pass/fail/exception.

---

**Summary of key tools:**

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|----------|-----------|
| Platform gate | `Assert.Inconclusive()` + `[TestCategory]` filter |
| CI skip | Environment check or `--filter` exclusion |
| Flaky retry | `[Retry(n)]` (MSTest v3.6+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` method |
